    "body": "[Reading over the high-level docs for Keychain](https://developer.apple.com/library/content/documentation/Security/Conceptual/keychainServConcepts/02concepts/concepts.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP30000897-CH204-SW11), specifically the \"Sharing Keychain Items\" section, it looks like code signing is required for an app to retain its Keychain access across recompiles. Specifically, the `keychain-access-group` entitlement seems to be governing. Unfortunately, this is at about the edge of my xcode experience. I did find these, which might help:\r\n\r\n1. Walkthrough of \"Configuring Keychain Sharing\" in xcode: https://developer.apple.com/library/content/documentation/IDEs/Conceptual/AppDistributionGuide/AddingCapabilities/AddingCapabilities.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40012582-CH26-SW15\r\n1. An iOS project's experience with setting up keychain sharing: https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/issues/4397\r\n"
